Create the Filter and Title 12

 

Create the Filter and Title






Step 10.1 Year Filter

Start by selecting the Shootings Per Year Card.

Copy and paste it.

Make it larger.

Replace the measure .Shootings Per Year with the column Year.

Change the visualization from card to slicer.

In the format tab, search for title.

Turn off the slicer header

Change the title to Year.





Change the size and coordinates to the following values:





In the format tab, search slider

Change the color to Blue (12239e).

In the Numeric inputs option, change the Text size to 10 and the Font family to DIN.

Activate the shadow option.

 



Step 10.2 - Clear Filter Button

This button is just an image. Get it from the attached files.

Change the size and coordinates to the following values:

At this point this, no more configuration is needed for this element.

Activate the shadow option.

 


 



Step 10.3 Demo button

Insert a blank button

Change the size and coordinates to the following values:





Turn off the outline option

Turn on the button text option.

Type in Demo in the button text box.

Change the font color to red (#FF000E)

At this point this, no more configuration is needed for this element.

Activate the shadow option.

 

 

 


Step 10.4 Create the Title

From the Weapon Type TP page, copy the 1st card, the weapon card.

Go back to the Dashboard and paste it.

Change the size and coordinates to the following values:




Create the measure: .Title = "US Mass Shootings"

Replace the measure Weapon with the measure .Title.

Change the font size of the Data label to 25 pt.

Activate the shadow option.

 

 

 

Step 10.5 Add the pictures to the title

Add the attached pictures to the Dashboard and modify the size and coordinates.

Colaberry Logo size and coordinates





Gun sizes and coordinates.






Step 10.6 Clear filters button bookmark

Go to View Tab

Click on Bookmarks

Click on Add

Bookmark 1 will appear.

Rename it to Clear Filters.

Set the Date chart to the month hierarchy level.

Make sure nothing else is filtered in your dashboard.

Click on the ellipsis of the bookmark.

Click on update.

Select the Clear filter Image.

Go to the Action tab.

Select bookmark as Type

In the next field, select Clear Filters as bookmark.

 



Step 10.7 Demo button website

Go to the Action tab.

Select Web URL as Type

In the next field, Web URL, paste a link or video to show all the features of the dashboard.

Here is the link used for the Dashboard.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1ooBlmtLnzrCH8SpuSpZk52vCjRwJyA7N/view?usp=sharing

 



And thats it!

Dashboard completed!
